<!--Hand 01 45 top left--><!--Hand 02 64763 top right--><!--headed paper, printed italics<p rend="center">Newstead Abbey,</p>
<p rend="center">Mansfield, Notts.</p>--><!--end of headed type-->
<lb/><p rend="right">6 <choice><abbr>Dec<hi rend="sup"><hi rend="underline">r</hi></hi></abbr><expan>December</expan></choice> 1864</p>
<lb/><p>Dear Sir</p>
<lb/><p>I thank you 
<lb/>very much for 
<lb/>the kindly feeling 
<lb/>which prompted 
<lb/>you to invite me 
<lb/>to a missionary 
<lb/>meeting at Leeds, 
<lb/>but I had previously 
<lb/>declined to make 
<lb/>any public 

	<pb n="0002" facs="liv_002132_0002"/><!--pb/@n='2'-->
<lb/>appearance there 
<lb/>not from any 
<lb/>dislike to the place 
<lb/>or people but 
<lb/>on account of 
<lb/>wishing to spend 
<lb/>my time at home 
<lb/>in a work which 
<lb/>I hope may do 
<lb/>more good than 
<lb/>could be expected 
<lb/>from my stammering 
<lb/>tongue. I wish to 
<lb/>let it be known 
<lb/>to the public how our 

	<pb n="0003" facs="liv_002132_0003"/><!--pb/@n='3'-->
<lb/>efforts have been 
<lb/>baffled by the slave 
<lb/>trading Portuguese 
<lb/>and the book ought 
<lb/>to have been finished 
<lb/>by this time and 
<lb/>the author away 
<lb/>again. So I am 
<lb/>sure you will 
<lb/>kindly excuse me</p>
<lb/><p>You could not 
<lb/>have loved bishop 
<lb/>Mackenzie more 
<lb/>than I did. I had 
<lb/>him in the Pioneer 
<lb/>some six months 

	<pb n="0004" facs="liv_002132_0004"/><!--pb/@n='4'-->
<lb/>&amp; the more he was 
<lb/>known the better he 
<lb/>was liked. I deeply 
<lb/>grieve that his 
<lb/>mission has been 
<lb/>suspended for I 
<lb/>have no doubt but that 
<lb/>in time he would 
<lb/>have changed the 
<lb/>state of the country</p>
<lb/><p>With a kind salutation</p>
<lb/><p rend="center">I am &amp;c</p>
<lb/><p>David Livingstone</p>
<lb/><p><choice><abbr>Rev<hi rend="sup"><hi rend="underline">d</hi></hi></abbr><expan>Reverend</expan></choice><choice><abbr>D<hi rend="sup"><hi rend="underline">r</hi></hi></abbr><expan>Doctor</expan></choice> Atley</p>
			
